{
  "texts": [
    "The interview transcript was formatted so that the interviewer's statements were prefaced with \"Interviewer:\" and the participant's responses were prefaced with \"Participant:\".",
    "Due to the inherent variability in the outcomes of large language models (LLMs) 49 and the temperature parameter being set to 0.3, which introduces variations in predicted scores, the average scores from three trials were considered.",
    "To test our hypothesis of a high correlation between the actual SPIN scores and GPT-4 SPIN score predictions, a Pearson correlation was conducted, followed by a t-test for significance.",
    "Since demographic data and SPIN data were collected in two different surveys to ensure anonymity, the two datasets had to be fused by participant code.",
    "In two cases, two datasets existed for the same participant code."
  ]
}